docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump again succeeded in turning back bipartisan congressional efforts to rebuke his lock-step support for Saudi Arabia after the Senate on Monday failed to override his veto on a series of measures that would have blocked billions of dollars of arms sales to the Persian Gulf region.

docs.abstract: Congress and the White House found a way to come together on guns 25 years ago. It is hard to see that kind of bipartisanship resurfacing in the current environment.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Bill Clinton had just been ambushed by his own party. docs.abstract: While there is widespread agreement on the need to protect American interests in space, there is disagreement on how to go about it.
docs.snippet: While there is widespread agreement on the need to protect American interests in space, there is disagreement on how to go about it.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump on Thursday authorized the creation of the United States Space Command, citing the need for a centralized unit to protect American interests in what he called “the next war-fighting domain.” He described the command as a precursor to the Space Force, a sixth branch of the military that he has promised to supporters at his rallies and that he wants Congress to create.

headline.main: Trump Authorizes a Space Command. Next, He Wants a Space Force.
headline.print_headline: Space Force Must Wait, But Trump Authorizes Initial Command Unit

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The former F.B.I. director James B. Comey violated policy by disclosing memos about his interactions with President Trump to people outside the bureau, said a blistering Justice Department inspector general report released on Thursday. The report admonished him for setting “a dangerous example” for officials with access to government secrets.

headline.main: Comey Is Criticized by Justice Dept. Watchdog for Violating F.B.I. Rules

docs.abstract: After shootings in Dayton and El Paso last month, the issue was already expected to top the agenda when lawmakers return from their recess next week. Now the pressure has intensified.
docs.snippet: After shootings in Dayton and El Paso last month, the issue was already expected to top the agenda when lawmakers return from their recess next week. Now the pressure has intensified.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The deadly shooting spree in West Texas this weekend — the latest in an especially gruesome summer of massacres — has intensified pressure on congressional Republicans to take up gun safety legislation, giving fresh urgency to a debate that was already expected to be at the top of lawmakers’ agenda when they return to the Capitol next week.

headline.main: Texas Shooting Brings New Urgency to Gun Debate in Congress
headline.print_headline: Texas Shooting Adds Urgency In Washington

docs.abstract: White House advisers want to expand the C.I.A.’s presence as troops leave Afghanistan, but the agency’s director and others expressed reservations.
docs.snippet: White House advisers want to expand the C.I.A.’s presence as troops leave Afghanistan, but the agency’s director and others expressed reservations.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senior White House advisers have proposed secretly expanding the C.I.A.’s presence in Afghanistan if international forces begin to withdraw from the country, according to American officials. But C.I.A. and military officials have expressed reservations, prompting a debate in the administration that could complicate negotiations with the Taliban to end the war.

headline.main: Trump Administration Officials at Odds Over C.I.A.’s Role in Afghanistan
headline.print_headline: White House Rift Over C.I.A.’s Role In Afghan Battle
